<h1 id="define-configuration-route">Define configuration route</h1>


<p>This procedure focuses on defining a configuration route that determines the sequence in which the configuration groups will be presented. The demo data company used to create this procedure is USMF. This is the sixth procedure out of eight that explains how to build combinations for dimension-based configuration.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to Product information management &gt; Bills of materials and formulas &gt; Bills of materials.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.</li>
<li>On the Action Pane, click Options.</li>
<li>Click Change view.</li>
<li>Click Header view.</li>
<li>Expand or collapse the Configuration route section.</li>
<li>Click Add.</li>
<li>In the list, mark the selected row.</li>
<li>In the Configuration group field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Click Add.</li>
<li>In the list, mark the selected row.</li>
<li>In the Configuration group field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
